# ATM Verification Framework for Secure Transaction Processing

[![Verilog](https://img.shields.io/badge/RTL-Verilog-blue)]()
[![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Verification-Python-green)]()
[![Tests](https://img.shields.io/badge/Tests-10%20Passing-brightgreen)]()
[![Coverage](https://img.shields.io/badge/Coverage-State%20%26%20Transition-orange)]()

A hardware verification project that models secure ATM transactions using a **Finite State Machine (FSM)** in Verilog and validates its correctness through an automated **Python-based verification framework** featuring randomized testing, coverage analysis, and interactive reporting.

---

## Architecture Overview

```text
                    +----------------+
                    |   Python API   |
                    +--------+-------+
                             |
                             v
                    +----------------+
                    | Testbench Gen   |
                    +--------+-------+
                             |
                             v
                    +----------------+
                    |  ATM FSM (RTL) |
                    |    Verilog     |
                    +--------+-------+
                             |
                             v
                    +----------------+
                    |  Icarus Verilog|
                    |   Simulation   |
                    +--------+-------+
                             |
           +----------------+----------------+
           |                                 |
           v                                 v
+------------------+             +------------------+
| Coverage Reports |             | HTML Dashboard   |
+------------------+             +------------------+
```

---

# Features

- ✅ 12-state ATM Finite State Machine in Verilog
- ✅ Card authentication and PIN verification
- ✅ Three-attempt account lockout mechanism
- ✅ Withdrawal limit and insufficient balance detection
- ✅ Automated Verilog testbench generation
- ✅ Randomized and edge-case verification
- ✅ State and transition coverage collection
- ✅ Interactive HTML dashboard
- ✅ GTKWave waveform debugging
- ✅ One-command regression execution

